## Key Engineering Guardrails for Your Backend

   1. Token Truncation Safety: When passing the extracted text to DeepSeek or Claude for "Advanced Analysis" (generating step-by-step solutions or tagging difficulty), chunk the input per question block instead of uploading a full 3-hour mock test paper at once. This avoids context drifting and saves on API operational costs.
   2. Deterministic Layout Extraction: Do not rely on LLMs to tell you where to slice images. Use deterministic libraries like OpenCV alongside layout anchors generated by local models to slice diagrams sharply.
   3. KaTeX Compatibility: Ensure that whatever LaTeX format Marker or Gemini outputs uses standard notation (e.g., standard dollar sign arrays $...$ or $$...$$) so your web front-end framework can render the math natively on the client browser without lagging the CBT timer.

